Unusual long and overly specific words used to be a huge thing in redditor 2010s culture, but this one is definitely special in its origin and age. It actually appears in Patrick O'Brian's works even though he did not attend Eton himself.

Eton College inside joke: "Floccinaucinihilipilification", from Latin floccus (“a wisp”) + naucum (“a trifle”) + nihilum (“nothing”) + pilus (“a hair”) + -fication, "The act or habit of describing or regarding something as unimportant, of having no value or being worthless"
